import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['net_generation'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of net electricity generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Electricity Generation (MWh)')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['source'])['net_generation'].sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['source'], data['net_generation'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Energy Source')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Electricity Generation (MWh)')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of net electricity generation by energy source?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['net_generation'] = data['net_generation'] / data['net_generation'].sum() * 100
    data = data.groupby('source').sum()
    chart = data.plot.pie(y='net_generation', figsize=(8, 8), autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90)
    plt.title('What is the percentage contribution of each energy source towards net electricity generation?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'source'])['net_generation'].sum().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sources = data['source'].unique()
    for i, source in enumerate(sources):
        source_data = data[data['source'] == source]
        ax.bar(source_data['year'], source_data['net_generation'], label=source, color=f'C{i}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Electricity Generation (MWh)')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of net electricity generation for each energy source over the years?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    data.boxplot(column='net_generation', by='source', ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Energy Source')
    ax.set_ylabel('Net Electricity Generation (MWh)')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net electricity generation for each energy source?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
